 in tropical lowland areas may encounter intensified drought stresses, and thus, become more vulnerable to future climate change. Our results serve as an early indicator of potential effects of climate change on tropical pine species and raise concerns about sustainable managements of pine forests under a changing climate.},
author = {Rakthai, Sakkarin and Fu, Pei-Li and Fan, Ze-Xin and Gaire, Narayan Prasad and Pumijumnong, Nathsuda and Eiadthong, Wichan and Tangmitcharoen, Suwan},
